OL,3,C'Get on' with fixing the 'broken
OL,4,Croads', Keir Starmer tells councils
OL,6,FThe increase is estimated to be enough
OL,7,Fto fix around seven million potholes.
OL,9,FStarmer said: "Broken roads can risk
OL,10,Flives and cost families hundreds if
OL,11,Fnot thousands of pounds on repairs.
OL,12,FThat's a cost that can easily be
OL,13,Favoided by investing properly in our
OL,14,Froads.
OL,16,F"Through our Plan for Change we're
OL,17,Fdetermined to put more money back into
OL,18,Fthe pockets of hardworking people and
OL,19,Fimprove living standards.
